<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1820" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1820">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 871.001/6.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                King <persName type="to">Ferdinand</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>On this sad occasion of the death of your illustrious uncle, I wish to
                            express the earnest hope that Your Majesty’s reign will mark an era of
                            great prosperity. I also offer to Your Majesty the assurances of my
                            highest regards and good wishes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>